<div id="review_4080924063" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4080924063" />
    <a title="Shoane Clark" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/95228726-shoane-clark"><img alt="Shoane Clark" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4080924063?book_show_action=true">Jun 27, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Shoane Clark" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Shoane Clark" href="/user/show/95228726-shoane-clark">Shoane Clark</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4080924063" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11444271561910782361"><strong>A Incredible Read </strong><br/><br/>I loved this book from the beginning to the end. It had a lot of suspense in it, with a little twist. ﻿Pulled over in America? When you&apos;re white, you might get a ticket. When you&apos;re black, you might end up dead.In a fictional Michigan town, a man is pulled over by the local police. The driver wonders: “What did I do wrong?” The author did a wonderful job with this Legal Thriller Book. This book touched all aspects of what was really going on in this book. I see that this is Boo</span>
  <span id="freeText11444271561910782361" style="display:none"><strong>A Incredible Read </strong><br /><br />I loved this book from the beginning to the end. It had a lot of suspense in it, with a little twist. ﻿Pulled over in America? When you're white, you might get a ticket. When you're black, you might end up dead.In a fictional Michigan town, a man is pulled over by the local police. The driver wonders: “What did I do wrong?” The author did a wonderful job with this Legal Thriller Book. This book touched all aspects of what was really going on in this book. I see that this is Book 4, which is amazing, however, you must read the first three books, to really understand the full extent of this book. To me this has to be the most hard-hitting and emotive book of the series. I can honestly say that this book is fantastic, and as a reader, I must get the rest of the books to read these wonderful books. In this book the author showed his true talent, which showed that he is a bold author that is attuned to the conflicts that trouble the American people. This book helped me to understand what the author was really trying to imply to his readers in this book. The plot of this book regarding police brutality against people of colour is obviously a very delicate subject and has been portrayed perfectly by the author "Mark M. Bello. After reading this book, you can tell that the author has a vivid detailed way of writing and grasping his readers into this book. I know that I was amazed at the detailed information that was put into this book. This is aan astounding story of a family destroyed in a sheer moment of unjustifiable racism. A husband, wife, and their 2 children driving home from a beautiful day out is pulled over by a police officer. These type of events still happen in today's society, due to racism. The officer, either scared for his life or simply careless with the lives of colored people, shoots the husband right in front of his wife and two young girls. The story is told from the eyes of the family, trying to survive the most tragic thing that has happened to them, as well as from the eyes of the police officer who shot him and the lawyers and officials who defend them both. This story had its sad parts in it, especially the wife and two children witnessing their father getting shot right in front of them for no apparent reason. I applaud the author for this wonderful story, and I will definitely be getting the first three books as well. I highly recommend this book to be purchased and read, because as a reader you will not be disappointed. I give this book five stars. 🌟🌟🌟🌟🌟. </span>
  <a data-text-id="11444271561910782361" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
