        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3821165017" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer749660868927882344">I have rarely read a more truthful book. If you&apos;re aware of the racial injustice in this nation, you may find it stating the obvious. But if you&apos;re willfully or simply ignored it, or even agree with it, then this book has true lessons to teach the reader.<br/>It&apos;s also a great, involving story, from the beginning to end. It&apos;s also realistic. Solutions may be offered, and I wish our nation was mature enough to take them, but it&apos;s always &quot;two steps forward, one and a half steps back&quot; when it comes to A</span>
  <span id="freeText749660868927882344" style="display:none">I have rarely read a more truthful book. If you're aware of the racial injustice in this nation, you may find it stating the obvious. But if you're willfully or simply ignored it, or even agree with it, then this book has true lessons to teach the reader.<br />It's also a great, involving story, from the beginning to end. It's also realistic. Solutions may be offered, and I wish our nation was mature enough to take them, but it's always "two steps forward, one and a half steps back" when it comes to American racial justice.<br />It's no coincidence that the lawyer setting things straight is Jewish. My Jewish daughter lives in the South and due to her job is subjected to online and email and other death threats and insults to the point where she does not feel safe at work, or even out of work.<br />The ex-President is given a new name, but his allowing racist behavior to come more out in the open is reprehensible to the meaning of our country. <br />It doesn't sugar coat, and it doesn't give a false sense of progress, just a reality that every one of us has to work to change. <br />Well worth the time to read it, and the thoughts that it will create.<br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="749660868927882344" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

