<div id="review_3506735714" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3506735714" />
    <a title="Moná" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/20761553-mon"><img alt="Moná" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1547305094p2/20761553.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3506735714?book_show_action=true">Sep 02, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Moná" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Moná" href="/user/show/20761553-mon">Moná</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781732447172" href="/book/show/54207927-betrayal-in-black">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3506735714" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17775531842688019606">We&apos;re living in a challenging time in America, especially when it comes to the racial wars within our country. We have always been divided somehow, but this is the first time a major uproar has manifested into something we can no longer keep a lid on. Emotions are at an all-time high and many want answers to these dilemmas. Is there a chance we could ever become the world we&apos;ve been dreamt of becoming?<br/><br/>In &quot;Betrayal in Black (A Zachary Blake Legal Thriller Book 4),&quot; author Mark M. Bello sheds ligh</span>
  <span id="freeText17775531842688019606" style="display:none">We're living in a challenging time in America, especially when it comes to the racial wars within our country. We have always been divided somehow, but this is the first time a major uproar has manifested into something we can no longer keep a lid on. Emotions are at an all-time high and many want answers to these dilemmas. Is there a chance we could ever become the world we've been dreamt of becoming?<br /><br />In "Betrayal in Black (A Zachary Blake Legal Thriller Book 4)," author Mark M. Bello sheds light on one of the most controversial topics occurring in America, even in today's world, police brutality and civil suits of unjust due to race. Unfortunately, a young black husband and father was the newest victim to a fatality at the hands of a white police officer at an unnecessary traffic stop. There are quite a few individuals whose aim is to seek justice on the behalf of his widow and children. The prosecutor, Lawrence Bialy alongside a civil trial lawyer, Zachary Blake, are two individuals who truly believe this case can put a dent to Detroit's image of equal justice. By banding together, the widow possibly stands a chance at reaping the benefits deserved for the tragic loss of her husband. As a reader, there will be mixed emotions and conflict within learning all sides of this case, giving you a sense that you are a witness watching everything unfold before your eyes.<br /><br />I am glad to have read this book as it was well written in providing all sides of an ugly situation, allowing the reader to understand the dangers of both sides of the fence. Through this reading experience, I have learned a lot more about the law in terms of what punishments can be granted should police step out of line. What is interesting in this case is just how quick the officer felt he was being the "scapegoat" of the precinct and how he felt ostracize from his blue brothers. I great book and I highly recommend everyone to read it.</span>
  <a data-text-id="17775531842688019606" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


